splash: collapse to a single full-bleed surface (no native icon stage)

Screenshots from the device showed two splash screens in sequence:
first the native cold-start splash (orange background with the
Talaa artwork as a centred icon), then the Dart SplashPage with the
artwork as a full-bleed cover.  The user wants only the second one
visible.

Fix: drop the image from the native splash entirely, leaving just a
plain brand-orange flat colour as the cold-start backdrop.  Because
SplashPage paints the same orange colour and immediately covers the
entire screen with the artwork via BoxFit.cover, the visible
sequence collapses to:

    [orange flash] -> [full-bleed splash artwork] -> [home]

i.e. one splash screen, no centred-icon stage between cold-start
and the in-app splash.

Changes
* pubspec.yaml: removed the image: / image_dark: keys from both the
  top-level flutter_native_splash block and the android_12 block.
  Kept color: #FF6B35 / color_dark: #14100C so the flash is the
  same orange the Dart side paints.
* Re-ran dart run flutter_native_splash:create so all Android
  drawables and the iOS launch storyboard regenerated as plain
  colour fills (no bitmap layer).
* lib/pages/splash_page.dart: tightened the inline comment to
  describe the new single-surface flow accurately.

flutter analyze: 0 issues across the workspace.
